docs.abstract: The move comes as United States and European leaders grow increasingly skeptical of Chinese deals, often citing concerns about national security.
docs.snippet: The move comes as United States and European leaders grow increasingly skeptical of Chinese deals, often citing concerns about national security.
docs.lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — Canada has blocked a $1 billion takeover of a construction company by a state-controlled Chinese company over national security concerns, a rare move by a government that until now has largely welcomed such deals despite growing skepticism over Chinese money elsewhere.

headline.main: Canada Blocks Chinese Takeover on Security Concerns
headline.print_headline: Canada Halts Chinese Deal Over Security Concerns

docs.abstract: Self-driving technology could one day turn your car into a mobile living room. That has companies trying to figure out how to even out the roughest spots of the road to the future.
docs.snippet: Self-driving technology could one day turn your car into a mobile living room. That has companies trying to figure out how to even out the roughest spots of the road to the future.
docs.lead_paragraph: WOBURN, Mass. — The obstacle course was a series of speed bumps in a parking lot at the headquarters of ClearMotion, a supplier of high-tech chassis parts for production cars. The challengers were a late-model Mercedes-Benz and a 2016 BMW 535i equipped with the company’s technology — an electrically powered hydraulic device meant to complement the venerable shock absorber and keep the passenger compartment as level as possible.

headline.main: Seeking a Smoother Ride, Whether You Drive or Your Autonomous Car Does
headline.print_headline: Soothing the Shock From the Bumps in the Road

docs.abstract: The Walt Disney Company struck a deal in December to buy most of 21st Century Fox, but Comcast, which has pursued Fox in the past, thinks it has another opening.
docs.snippet: The Walt Disney Company struck a deal in December to buy most of 21st Century Fox, but Comcast, which has pursued Fox in the past, thinks it has another opening.
docs.lead_paragraph: On Wednesday, Comcast confirmed in a statement that it was in the “advanced stages of preparing”  its own bid for the 21st Century Fox assets that Walt Disney has agreed to buy.

headline.main: As Disney Moves Forward With Fox, Comcast Continues Plotting
headline.print_headline: How Comcast May Make Move On Disney’s Big Deal for Fox

docs.abstract: Mary Barra said that the United States should not scrap the trade pact and that any changes should account for the interests of American automakers and workers.

docs.lead_paragraph: PHOENIX — For more than half a century, Phoenix ignored its warehouse district, leaving the area dormant with aging buildings ripe for vandalism. The eyesore felt eerie at night, and no one stepped foot there in the day.

headline.main: A Renewal for Phoenix’s Warehouse District: Polished but Gritty
headline.print_headline: A Phoenix District Gets Some Polish but Keeps Its Grit

docs.abstract: Once notorious for “dead bodies, floating cars and nefarious activities,” the river is in the midst of a renewal, including plans for a Major League Soccer stadium nearby.
docs.snippet: Once notorious for “dead bodies, floating cars and nefarious activities,” the river is in the midst of a renewal, including plans for a Major League Soccer stadium nearby.
docs.lead_paragraph: MIAMI — As it meandered through downtown, the Miami River was for years a slovenly mess, its shores lined with small, scrappy shipyards, bait-and-tackle shops and low-rent marinas with rotting piers. When decrepit vessels sank, they were often left where they lay, hulls protruding from the oily water.

headline.main: Along Miami River, Derelict Bait Shops Give Way to Luxury Condos
headline.print_headline: In Miami, a River With a Shady Past Is Gleaming Again
